Do we actually need this? Couldn't we simplify the model significantly and remove the extra pieces we aren't using?

For tests, I think we only really need...

```
@Entity()
export class Test {
  @PrimaryColumn()
  id: number;

  // JSONB column
  @Column("jsonb", {nullable: true})
  json?: any;
}
```

We don't even need to read the data in the json blob, right?  We can compare the `id` values & make sure the sort order is correct in that way.
